xanim
------------------------------------------
Xanim is a (extremely old) program for playing a wide variety of
animation, audio and video formats on unix X11 machines.

NOTE: Audio does not work on Cygwin.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.5.24-2
  libX11_6-1.1.1-1
  libXext6-1.0.2-1
  libXt6-1.0.4-1
  zlib-1.2.3-2

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  cygwin-1.5.24-2
  binutils-20060817-1
  cygport-0.2.11-1
  gawk-3.1.5-4
  gcc-core-3.4.4-3
  make-3.81-1
  sed-4.1.5-2

Canonical website:
  http://xanim.polter.net/

Canonical download:
  http://xanim.polter.net/files/xanim2801.tar.gz

LICENSING: 
  Only 'non-commercial' usage is allowed.  As this is not compatible with
  the Cygwin DLL, binary packages of xanim should not be distributed.

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack xanim-2.80.1-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./xanim-2.80.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/xanim-2.80.1-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/xanim-2.80.1-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

